TestNG:  Annotations, Assertions

Test NG is a unit testing framework. (Test NG (Text-Next Generation) . It has flexiblity with annotations, data provider, priorities, dependencies, ignore test. Junit is mostlyl known alternative for TestNG.

Some Fundamental Annotations:

@Test: This is the main annotation. Makes the test runnable.

@BeforeClass: Get executed once before all tests.

@AfterClass: Gets executed once after all tests.

@Before Method : Gets executed before each test.

@AfterMethod: Gets executed after each test.

Note: There are some more annotations like (BeforeSuit, AfterSuit, BeforeTest, AfterTest) . These are mostly used with XML.

